<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1021" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1021">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Woodford</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-24"><hi rend="italic">February 24,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 139.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am instructed by the Secretary of the
                            Navy to instruct you to express to the Spanish Government his high
                            appreciation of the services rendered and honors paid by the Cuban
                            authorities to the officers and men of the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi> on the occasion of the public funeral of the members of
                            the crew lost in the disaster.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>